Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced); 
mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4 servings). Drain 
@pineapple{4%oz}(drained, reserving juice); roughly chop. Roughly chop 
@cilantro{1/4%oz}(roughly chopped). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and 
quartered). Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(halved, 
cored and thinly sliced) into strips.

In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (11/2 cups for 4 
servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce 
to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine minced onion, chopped pineapple, 
half the cilantro, and a big squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and 
@pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add 
sliced onion and green pepper; season with half the @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tbsp} 
(you'll use the rest in the next step), salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring 
occasionally, until veggies are browned and softened, ~{7-9%minutes}.

> TIP: If seasoning begins to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{} and cover to keep warm. Wipe out 
pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add 
@diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%oz}; using a #spatula{}, press into an even 
layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid. Swap in chicken (no 
> need to break up into pieces!) or beef for turkey.

Break up meat into pieces and stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}, remaining 
@Southwest Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, and reserved pineapple juice. Bring to a simmer 
and cook until sauce has thickened and turkey is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} 
more. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in lime zest, remaining cilantro, and 
@butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between bowls and top with turkey, veggies, and pineapple salsa. 
Drizzle with @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp} and serve with remaining lime 
wedges on the side.